title <size:18>File Filtering API - Class Diagram (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Find all .java files > 1MB modified in last 7 days, sorted by size." Follow Step 1 to 7.</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE — FileFilterService
' ====================================================================
class FileFilterService <<Facade>> {
    - fileSource : FileSource
    - defaultFilter : Filter
    --
    + search(filter) : List<File>
    + search(filter, comparator) : List<File>
    + count(filter) : int
    + findFirst(filter) : File
    + exists(filter) : boolean
}

note top of FileFilterService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Client calls search(filter) with any
    filter combination. This **Facade**
    hides how files are fetched (local disk,
    S3, database) and applies the filter."

    "Example: service.search(
      new AndFilter(sizeFilter, extFilter)
    )"
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: FILE MODEL
' ====================================================================
class File {
    - name : String
    - extension : String
    - size : long
    - path : String
    - lastModified : LocalDateTime
    - createdAt : LocalDateTime
    - isDirectory : boolean
    - permissions : Set<Permission>
    --
    + getName() : String
    + getExtension() : String
    + getSize() : long
    + getPath() : String
    + getLastModified() : LocalDateTime
    + isDirectory() : boolean
    + isHidden() : boolean
}

enum Permission {
    READ
    WRITE
    EXECUTE
}

note top of File #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - What are we filtering?**
    "A File has name, extension, size, path,
    timestamps, and permissions.
    These are the **attributes** we filter on.
    Pure data model, no logic." **(SRP)**
end note

File --> Permission : has >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: FILE SOURCE — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface FileSource <<Strategy>> {
    + listFiles() : List<File>
    + listFiles(directory) : List<File>
}

class LocalFileSource {
    - rootPath : String
    --
    + listFiles() : List<File>
    + listFiles(directory) : List<File>
}

class InMemoryFileSource {
    - files : List<File>
    --
    + listFiles() : List<File>
    + addFile(file) : void
}

class S3FileSource {
    - bucketName : String
    - s3Client : S3Client
    --
    + listFiles() : List<File>
    + listFiles(prefix) : List<File>
}

note bottom of FileSource #C8E6C9
    **STEP 3 - Where do files come from?**
    "Could be local disk, in-memory (tests),
    or cloud (S3). **Strategy Pattern** —
    FileFilterService depends on FileSource
    interface, not concrete source."

    "Swap LocalFileSource for S3FileSource
    without changing any filter logic."
    **Pattern: Strategy | DIP, OCP**
end note

FileSource <|.. LocalFileSource
FileSource <|.. InMemoryFileSource
FileSource <|.. S3FileSource
FileFilterService --> FileSource : reads from >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: FILTER INTERFACE — Core Abstraction (Strategy)
' ====================================================================
interface Filter <<Strategy>> {
    + apply(file : File) : boolean
}

note top of Filter #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - The core abstraction.**
    "One interface, one method: apply(file).
    Returns true if file passes the filter.
    Every filter — simple or complex —
    implements this same interface.
    This is the **Strategy Pattern** foundation.
    The system is built around this."
    **Pattern: Strategy | ISP, OCP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: CONCRETE FILTERS — Leaf Strategies
' ====================================================================
class SizeFilter {
    - minSize : long
    - maxSize : long
    - operator : ComparisonOperator
    --
    + apply(file) : boolean
}

class ExtensionFilter {
    - extensions : Set<String>
    --
    + apply(file) : boolean
}

class NameFilter {
    - pattern : String
    - regex : boolean
    --
    + apply(file) : boolean
}

class DateFilter {
    - after : LocalDateTime
    - before : LocalDateTime
    - dateField : DateField
    --
    + apply(file) : boolean
}

class PermissionFilter {
    - requiredPermissions : Set<Permission>
    --
    + apply(file) : boolean
}

class DirectoryFilter {
    - includeDirectories : boolean
    --
    + apply(file) : boolean
}

enum ComparisonOperator {
    GREATER_THAN
    LESS_THAN
    EQUAL_TO
    BETWEEN
}

enum DateField {
    CREATED
    MODIFIED
}

note bottom of SizeFilter #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Leaf filters (one criterion each).**
    "Each filter checks ONE attribute:
    **SizeFilter**: file > 1MB? (uses operator)
    **ExtensionFilter**: .java, .py, .txt?
    **NameFilter**: matches pattern/regex?
    **DateFilter**: modified after X date?
    **PermissionFilter**: has WRITE access?
    **DirectoryFilter**: skip directories?"

    "Each is a **Strategy** — pluggable, testable,
    single responsibility."
    **Pattern: Strategy | SRP, OCP**
end note

Filter <|.. SizeFilter
Filter <|.. ExtensionFilter
Filter <|.. NameFilter
Filter <|.. DateFilter
Filter <|.. PermissionFilter
Filter <|.. DirectoryFilter
SizeFilter --> ComparisonOperator
DateFilter --> DateField


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: COMPOSITE FILTERS — AND, OR, NOT (Composite Pattern)
' ====================================================================
class AndFilter {
    - filters : List<Filter>
    --
    + AndFilter(filters)
    + apply(file) : boolean
}

class OrFilter {
    - filters : List<Filter>
    --
    + OrFilter(filters)
    + apply(file) : boolean
}

class NotFilter {
    - filter : Filter
    --
    + NotFilter(filter)
    + apply(file) : boolean
}

note top of AndFilter #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6 - Combine filters. (KEY STEP)**
    "This is the **Composite Pattern**. And, Or,
    Not are themselves Filters — they implement
    the same Filter interface."

    "**AndFilter**: ALL children must pass.
    **OrFilter**: ANY child must pass.
    **NotFilter**: inverts one child."

    "You can nest them:
    And(SizeFilter, Or(ExtFilter, NameFilter))
    This gives infinite composability with
    zero new code."
    **Pattern: Composite | OCP, LSP**
end note

Filter <|.. AndFilter
Filter <|.. OrFilter
Filter <|.. NotFilter
AndFilter o--> Filter : children >
OrFilter o--> Filter : children >
NotFilter o--> Filter : wraps >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: BUILDER — Fluent Filter Construction
' ====================================================================
class FilterBuilder <<Builder>> {
    - filters : List<Filter>
    --
    + minSize(bytes) : FilterBuilder
    + maxSize(bytes) : FilterBuilder
    + extensions(exts) : FilterBuilder
    + nameContains(pattern) : FilterBuilder
    + nameMatches(regex) : FilterBuilder
    + modifiedAfter(date) : FilterBuilder
    + modifiedBefore(date) : FilterBuilder
    + hasPermission(perm) : FilterBuilder
    + excludeDirectories() : FilterBuilder
    + or(filter) : FilterBuilder
    + not(filter) : FilterBuilder
    + build() : Filter
}

note top of FilterBuilder #D1C4E9
    **STEP 7 - Clean API for clients.**
    "Constructing And(Size, Ext, Date) by hand
    is verbose. **Builder Pattern** gives a
    fluent API:"

    "Filter f = new FilterBuilder()
      .minSize(1_000_000)
      .extensions("java", "kt")
      .modifiedAfter(lastWeek)
      .excludeDirectories()
      .build();  // returns AndFilter"

    "build() wraps all criteria in an AndFilter.
    Clean, readable, validated."
    **Pattern: Builder | SRP**
end note

FilterBuilder --> Filter : builds >
FilterBuilder --> AndFilter : default combines with >


' ====================================================================
'  SORTING (optional, complementary)
' ====================================================================
interface FileSortStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + sort(files) : List<File>
}

class SortBySize {
    - ascending : boolean
    --
    + sort(files) : List<File>
}

class SortByName {
    - ascending : boolean
    --
    + sort(files) : List<File>
}

class SortByDate {
    - field : DateField
    - ascending : boolean
    --
    + sort(files) : List<File>
}

FileSortStrategy <|.. SortBySize
FileSortStrategy <|.. SortByName
FileSortStrategy <|.. SortByDate
FileFilterService --> FileSortStrategy : optional sort >


' ====================================================================
'  FACADE CONNECTIONS
' ====================================================================
FileFilterService --> Filter : applies >
FileFilterService --> File : returns >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "The entire system is built around one interface:
    Filter.apply(file). Simple filters check one attribute (**Strategy**).
    Composite filters combine them with AND/OR/NOT (**Composite**).
    Builder provides a fluent API. FileSource is pluggable.
    The query 'all .java files > 1MB modified last week' becomes:
    FilterBuilder().extensions(java).minSize(1MB).modifiedAfter(lastWeek).build()
    4 patterns: **Strategy**, **Composite**, **Builder**, **Facade**."
end note


